Dev Log - 2026-05-12

Summary

truth-layer and marketing-contract hardening day

Today was about making the marketing generation path more honest and more repeatable. The work did not add a flashy new surface; it tightened the rules around what the generator is allowed to say, how it derives copy, and how we verify the outputs. That matters because marketing tooling is only useful if it stays tethered to the real project state instead of drifting into generic claims.

The day’s shape was a clean progression: define the truth model, wire a deterministic generator around it, then add fixtures and tests that prove the pipeline stays inside the contract. The result is a marketing flow that is much harder to accidentally inflate, easier to regress-test, and more suitable for producing evidence-bound output from real source material.

What I completed

Truth layer and reusable contracts

- Added the marketing truth layer and reusable skill contracts under `docs/Marketing/` and `guardian/skills/marketing/`.
- Defined the claim-truth model so generated marketing copy has a clearer boundary between supported claims, inferred claims, and unsupported claims.
- Added shared contract and template material for ad copy, channel variants, core briefs, and infographic generation.

Deterministic generator wiring

- Added the `generate-marketing` CLI and wired it into the repo command path.
- Expanded the marketing pipeline so generation is deterministic rather than ad hoc.
- Kept the generator logic aligned with the contract layer instead of letting prompts or templates imply capabilities the source material does not support.

Fixtures and pipeline coverage

- Added a fixture corpus and golden outputs for the marketing pipeline.
- Created review notes and run metadata for the campaign test corpus.
- Added test coverage around the generator path so the marketing pipeline can be checked against stable expected output.

Claim suitability gate

- Added a suitability gate for marketing claims so generated content can be screened before it becomes output.
- This makes the pipeline more conservative and more trustworthy, especially for copy that could otherwise overstate product state or proof.

Important outcome

The marketing system is no longer just a text generator wrapped around project docs. It now has enough structural truth to decide what can be said, what must stay tentative, and what should be blocked.

That changes the system in a practical way. Copy generation is now tied to a contract, a deterministic path, and a test corpus. The pipeline stopped being a loose content helper and started behaving more like an evidence-bound publishing system.

