Narrative Log

Dev Log - 2026-05-12

It was a contract day more than a feature day, and that is what made it matter.

The core shift was not “we can generate marketing copy now.” That would be too loose. The real change was that the marketing generator was forced to inherit the project’s truth instead of improvising around it. The new truth layer and reusable contracts gave the system a vocabulary for what counts as supportable claim material, what should be treated as inference, and what should simply be rejected. That is the kind of work that does not look dramatic in a diff, but it changes the character of the system.

From there, the generator was made deterministic and reachable through a real CLI path. That mattered because a marketing pipeline that depends on hand-shaped prompt behavior is too easy to drift. By wiring it into a command and making the pipeline explicit, the output becomes something we can inspect, rerun, and reason about. The system is less dependent on mood, less dependent on incidental prompt shape, and more dependent on code.

The fixture corpus and golden outputs finished the job. They gave the pipeline something concrete to be measured against. Instead of trusting that the generator “probably” stays within bounds, we now have examples, metadata, and tests that make the contract visible. The added suitability gate is the bluntest expression of that direction: if a claim does not clear the bar, it does not go out. That is a better failure mode than silently drifting into marketing language that outruns the product.

The important structural change is that marketing output is now closer to an evidence pipeline than a copywriting helper. It can still produce useful material, but it does so under a tighter discipline. That makes the surface more honest, easier to audit, and less likely to create accidental release noise.

What this makes possible next is straightforward: keep tightening the examples, extend the negative cases, and make sure any future marketing output continues to follow the same truth boundary instead of widening it by habit.


